5. 1 Samuel 17:41-50

1 Samuel 17:41 שמואל ב   וַיֵּלֶךְ הַפְּלִשְׁתִּי הֹלֵךְ וְקָרֵב אֶל־דָּוִד וְהָאִישׁ נֹשֵׂא הַצִּנָּה לְפָנָיו:

Verbs: 
a וַיֵּלֶךְ הַפְּלִשְׁתִּי OF:הָלַךְ, walk, come, Conj-w | V-Qal-ConsecImperf-3ms, and_he_walked, the_Philistine

b הֹלֵךְ וְקָרֵב אֶל־דָּוִד, OF:הָלַךְ, walk, come, V-Qal-Prtcpl-ms, walking, and_near -David

c וְהָאִישׁ נֹשֵׂא הַצִּנָּה לְפָנָיו, OF:נָשָֹא, bear, V-Qal-Prtcpl-ms, who_bore, the_man, who_bore, the_shield, before_him. 

Translation: And the Philistine walked, and walked near to David, and the man who bore the shield before him. 


1 Samuel 17:42 שמואל ב 17-42 וַיַּבֵּט הַפְּלִשְׁתִּי וַיִּרְאֶה אֶת־דָּוִד וַיִּבְזֵהוּ כִּי־הָיָה נַעַר וְאַדְמֹנִי עִם־יְפֵה מַרְאֶה:

a וַיַּבֵּט הַפְּלִשְׁתִּי, OF:נָבַט, look, Conj-w | V-Hifil-ConsecImperf-3ms, and_he_looked, the_Philistine, 

b וַיִּרְאֶה אֶת־דָּוִד, OF:רָאָה, see, Conj-w | V-Qal-ConsecImperf-3ms, and_he_saw, -David, 

c: וַיִּבְזֵהוּ, OF:בָּזָה, disdain, Conj-w | V-Qal-ConsecImperf-3ms | 3ms, and_he_disdained_him, 

d: כִּי־הָיָה נַעַר וְאַדְמֹנִי עִם־יְפֵה מַרְאֶה, OF: הָיָה, is, V-Qal-Perf-3ms, he_was, for, he_was, a_youth, and_ruddy, and_beautiful, good_looking(face). 

Translation: And the Philistine looked and saw David, he disdained him, for he was a youth, and ruddy红润, and beautiful, have a good looking face. 


